1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,880
 Hello, brothers and sisters.

2
00:00:01,880 --> 00:00:04,000
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

3
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,120
 So one things that I like to do in my free time

4
00:00:08,120 --> 00:00:10,940
 is I like to go climbing.

5
00:00:10,940 --> 00:00:13,240
 So naturally, my social media algorithms,

6
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:14,940
 they would always suggest to me all sorts

7
00:00:14,940 --> 00:00:17,760
 of climbing-related content.

8
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:19,600
 And a few months ago, I actually bumped

9
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,840
 into this very heartwarming YouTube shorts

10
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:25,160
 posted by-- she's a professional climber and also

11
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,160
 a former Olympian from the UK.

12
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:30,680
 And in this YouTube shorts, she brought her daughter

13
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:32,400
 to climb outdoors.

14
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:33,960
 And you can see that her daughter,

15
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:37,960
 she was very determined to climb this climb all by herself

16
00:00:37,960 --> 00:00:39,840
 without the mom's help.

17
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

18
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:00,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

19
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:11,840
 So a few moves into the climb, however,

20
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:14,800
 she started to panic a little bit when things

21
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:16,560
 got a little more challenging.

22
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:20,000
 And her emotions began to come out.

23
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,240
 You can see the dilemma here.

24
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:26,000
 On one hand, she wanted to do the climb all by herself.

25
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
 So she didn't want her mom to help her at all.

26
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:33,000
 But on the other hand, she was getting a little scared.

27
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,360
 And her natural instinct just came up

28
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:38,960
 to ask her mom for help.

29
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

30
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:04,760
 So I think we can all resonate with the feelings of the daughter

31
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:07,840
 here when we are faced with some sort of adversities

32
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,520
 and challenge, right?

33
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:11,320
 Maybe you're feeling stuck in your life.

34
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:13,680
 And you're just having a hard time figuring out

35
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,560
 what is the next steps.

36
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:18,280
 Or maybe you're in some sort of crisis moment.

37
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:22,080
 And you just can't seem to figure a way out.

38
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:26,480
 Or maybe some of us, you are confronted by your own fears.

39
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,720
 Will my marriage or my relationship last?

40
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:32,360
 Or what if I lose my job?

41
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,840
 Or what if my friends or people that I love

42
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:37,800
 actually abandon or leave me?

43
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:42,920
 And in these moments of doubt, how do you usually respond?

44
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:46,640
 What would you do in the face of adversity?

45
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:53,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

46
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:20,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

47
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,560
 So this morning, we are going to look

48
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:25,680
 at the third major judge in the book of "Judges," that

49
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:27,240
 is, Deborah.

50
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:30,520
 The cycle of Deborah is actually quite unique

51
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:33,200
 because it spans across two chapters.

52
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:37,080
 And it consists of a story and a song.

53
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:40,160
 So "Judges 4," that is the one that we'll be looking in today,

54
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,880
 is in the form of a story.

55
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:44,800
 That is the narrative portion of this cycle.

56
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:47,640
 While "Judges 5" is in the form of a poem.

57
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:50,600
 That is the song portion of this cycle.

58
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,480
 And so we'll actually spend two Sundays

59
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:55,080
 in this cycle of Deborah alone.

60
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:56,560
 But again, for this morning, we're

61
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:59,520
 going to focus on the narrative portion of the cycle.

62
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,960
 That is "Judges 4."

63
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:04,560
 And again, we will explore these questions together.

64
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:08,840
 What should we do in the face of adversities and doubt?

65
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:15,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

66
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:46,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

67
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:49,760
 And so today, instead of having the passage up on a screen

68
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,360
 and trying to do something different,

69
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:54,080
 so I want to encourage you to open your own Bible,

70
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:57,480
 physically or digitally, and follow along with our passage.

71
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:01,000
 Because there will be some clues that's earlier in our passage

72
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,960
 that will only get fully reviewed at the end.

73
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:05,960
 And I think it is actually more effective for us

74
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:09,540
 to learn from God's word by having the whole passage

75
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:12,320
 in our hand, rather than seeing it section by section

76
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:15,960
 on the screen, where I can only show a limited amount of verses

77
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:16,920
 every time.

78
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,420
 And if you don't have a Bible or you

79
00:05:18,420 --> 00:05:20,480
 don't have a way to access it, I also

80
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,160
 printed out a few physical copies

81
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,080
 that you can come up to the table and grab.

82
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:27,920
 And so to apologize, I forgot to print out the Mandarin version.

83
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:30,320
 So there's an English copy of "Judges 4"

84
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,800
 up there if you want to come up and grab them.

85
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

86
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:38,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

87
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:16,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

88
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,440
 OK, everyone ready?

89
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:22,320
 We're going to start with "Judges 4" verse 1.

90
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:26,720
 "So again, the Israelites did evil in the eyes of the Lord,

91
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:29,020
 now that Ehud was dead.

92
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:32,800
 So the Lord sold them into the hands of Jabin, king of Canaan,

93
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,800
 who reigned in Hazor.

94
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,820
 Sisera, the commander of his army,

95
00:06:36,820 --> 00:06:39,480
 was based in Harosheth Hagoyim.

96
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:42,360
 Because he and 900 chariots fitted with iron

97
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:45,760
 and had cruelly oppressed the Israelites for 20 years,

98
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:50,000
 they cried out to the Lord for help."

99
00:06:50,000 --> 00:07:13,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

100
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,180
 And so right here at the first verse,

101
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:18,080
 we're immediately being connected to our narrative

102
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:21,120
 back to the previous judge, that is Ehud.

103
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:23,380
 And if you recall from my previous sermon,

104
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:26,680
 after Ehud had defeated Eglon, king of Moab,

105
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:29,080
 the land of Israel, they enjoyed a period of peace

106
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:31,080
 for 80 years.

107
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:34,120
 But right after these 80 years, after Ehud had died,

108
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,000
 this cycle repeats itself again.

109
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:40,440
 And we see that Israel does evil in the eyes of the Lord.

110
00:07:40,440 --> 00:08:03,340
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

111
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:06,840
 And this time, the Lord actually used Jabin, king of Canaan,

112
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:10,720
 and also his commander, Sisera, to oppress Israel.

113
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:17,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

114
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:19,800
 One advantage of Sisera's army here

115
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:23,240
 was that they had 900 iron chariots.

116
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:25,880
 And so iron chariots was kind of like the top-of-the-line

117
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:29,140
 technology in warfare during that time.

118
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:33,720
 When a war is fought over on flat land or coastal plains,

119
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:36,960
 it actually provides a huge advantage for this iron chariots

120
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:40,160
 army compared to just regular foot soldiers.

121
00:08:40,160 --> 00:08:58,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

122
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:01,280
 And as a result of their oppressions from Sisera,

123
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:04,160
 Israel once again cried out to the Lord for help.

124
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:09,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

125
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:13,320
 And now let's look together in verse 4 and 5.

126
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:16,680
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

127
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:20,240
 Now Deborah, a prophet, the wife of Lapidoth,

128
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:23,200
 was leading or judging Israel at that time.

129
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,320
 She held court under the palm of Deborah

130
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:29,360
 between Ramah and Bethel in the hill country of Ephraim.

131
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:32,360
 And the Israelites went up to her to have their disputes

132
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,400
 decided.

133
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:48,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

134
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:51,920
 And so right here, we're being introduced to Deborah.

135
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:54,720
 Deborah was a prophetess by profession,

136
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:59,320
 or a more direct translation is that she was a woman prophet.

137
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:01,720
 I'm not going to spoil the rest of the story for you now,

138
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:05,560
 but women will actually play a significant role in our story

139
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,320
 today.

140
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:19,480
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

141
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:22,160
 And besides being a prophet or prophetess,

142
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:25,880
 we also learned that she was judging Israel at that time.

143
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,960
 And what this means is that Deborah, in some way,

144
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:30,480
 she was Israel's decision maker.

145
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:33,040
 And we see that people from all over Israel,

146
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:36,240
 they will come to her to have their dispute decided.

147
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:48,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

148
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:51,400
 And not only that, we will learn that she

149
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:54,440
 was also a representative and spoke person

150
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:57,480
 on behalf of the Lord in the following verses.

151
00:10:57,480 --> 00:11:04,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

152
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:07,320
 And so let's continue with verse 6.

153
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:09,560
 "She sent for Barak, son of Abinoam,

154
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:13,000
 from Kadesh in Naphtali, and say to him,

155
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,240
 the Lord, the God of Israel, commands you,

156
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:20,680
 go, take with you 10,000 men from Naphtali and Zebelin,

157
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:23,160
 and lead them up to Mount Tabor.

158
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:26,720
 I will lead Sisera, the commander of Jabin's army,

159
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:30,120
 with his chariots and his troops to the Kishon River

160
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,440
 and give him into your hands."

161
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:56,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

162
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:59,520
 And so even though Deborah, she was judging Israel

163
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:04,000
 at that time, she did not command the army of Israel.

164
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,040
 And so she sent for Barak.

165
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:09,080
 There are not many details about Barak here,

166
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:13,280
 but from what we can gather, he is from the tribe of Naphtali,

167
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:17,920
 and he was also chosen by God to be Israel's deliverer.

168
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:37,720
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

169
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,920
 And according to Deborah, Barak's role

170
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,240
 was pretty straightforward.

171
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:45,200
 That is, to go and to gather the troops to Mount Tabor

172
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:48,320
 and to call up the warriors from the tribes of Naphtali

173
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,880
 and Zebelin.

174
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:52,040
 And then the Lord himself, he will

175
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:56,320
 give Sisera and his army into the hands of Barak.

176
00:12:56,320 --> 00:13:14,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

177
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,920
 And so Deborah's message here is very clear.

178
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:22,080
 There is a command from God, and there's a promise of victory.

179
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:25,200
 And so the command is for Barak to gather his army

180
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,440
 and lead them into the battlefield.

181
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,360
 And then the promise is that the Lord

182
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:32,680
 will grant Israel their victory over Sisera and his army,

183
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:35,520
 even though Sisera has military advantage

184
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:37,680
 with his iron chariots.

185
00:13:37,680 --> 00:14:03,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

186
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:07,680
 But this is Barak's response here in verse 8.

187
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:11,960
 "Barak said to her, if you go with me, I will go.

188
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:15,600
 But if you don't go with me, then I won't go."

189
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:23,920
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

190
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:26,880
 So even though with the victory guaranteed,

191
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:30,320
 Barak, he still feel a little uncertain.

192
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:32,840
 And so he started to negotiate a little bit,

193
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:37,240
 giving Deborah his conditions or his terms for obedience.

194
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:42,160
 If you, Deborah, go with me, then I

195
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:44,200
 will obey your command and go.

196
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:48,880
 But if you don't go with me, then I won't go.

197
00:14:48,880 --> 00:15:07,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

198
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:10,720
 Barak's hesitancy here is not without reason.

199
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:13,360
 From a personal level, we learn that he

200
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:15,720
 is from the tribe of Naphtali.

201
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,240
 And when we go back to the first chapter in Judges,

202
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:20,160
 we see that the tribes of Naphtali

203
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:23,840
 actually failed to drive out the Canaanites living in their land.

204
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:27,760
 And so from Barak's perspective, this failure from his tribe

205
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,440
 might have added some doubts into his mind

206
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:33,720
 when he received this divine message from Deborah.

207
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:35,760
 And so instead of obeying, he shows

208
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:37,960
 some degree of disobedience.

209
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:49,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

210
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:11,440
 And if we take a step back and zoom out from this narrative

211
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:13,920
 back to the big picture of Judges,

212
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,720
 we know that the book of Judges in some way

213
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:18,240
 is an evaluation of whether or not

214
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:22,400
 Israel, as God's holy nation, will remain faithful

215
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,720
 and obedient to the Lord.

216
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,720
 And so as a nation, Barak's response

217
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:28,880
 here actually gave us some spiritual insights

218
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:31,800
 into the life of Israel's leaders,

219
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:34,600
 especially after the death of Moses and his successor,

220
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:35,720
 Joshua.

221
00:16:35,720 --> 00:17:00,560
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

222
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:05,680
 So now I want us to ask ourselves this question.

223
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:09,400
 What will we do in the face of adversities and doubts?

224
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,160
 And how will we respond when we're

225
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:15,840
 being asked to do something that we are not comfortable with?

226
00:17:15,840 --> 00:17:29,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

227
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:33,160
 I think we cannot relate to Barak in this situation.

228
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:35,280
 A lot of time, we want to trust God.

229
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:37,160
 We really want to trust God.

230
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:40,280
 But we want to trust him in our own terms

231
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:42,720
 or in ways that we are comfortable

232
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:45,160
 and that is convenient for us.

233
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:48,720
 And so our response may look like this.

234
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:52,960
 Lord, I will start giving if you give me a raise at my work.

235
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:55,920
 Or Lord, I will start loving my neighbor next door

236
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:59,560
 if they can just stop playing music so loud every night.

237
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:02,280
 Or Lord, I will start serving at church on Sunday

238
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:06,480
 if my boss would just stop scheduling me to work on Saturday.

239
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:35,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

240
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:41,920
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

241
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:45,000
 And do you see the issues here?

242
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,760
 Do you think God will be pleased with this kind of obedience

243
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:50,280
 and incomplete faith?

244
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:51,680
 In fact, it is well within reason

245
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:55,640
 for God to take offense with this kind of incomplete faith

246
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:58,400
 and half-hearted obedience, right?

247
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,880
 Just imagine this.

248
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:03,440
 If you ask your son to take the trash out after dinner,

249
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,480
 and this is how he responds to you,

250
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:08,720
 he says, yeah, sure, but only if you give me more pocket money

251
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:11,920
 or you increase my weekly allowance.

252
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:13,760
 If you are the parents here, you will probably

253
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:17,240
 feel quite disappointed and offended, right?

254
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:19,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

255
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:45,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

256
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:49,960
 However, we know that our God is a loving and patient father.

257
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:52,000
 And so even though Barak's faith is incomplete

258
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:55,920
 at this point of the story, God doesn't just abandon him,

259
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:59,160
 but he will patiently prove his own trustworthiness

260
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,160
 and faithfulness to Barak in order

261
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:03,760
 to rehabilitate Barak's faith.

262
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:22,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

263
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:24,400
 So let's come back to our passage

264
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:27,120
 here and continue in verse 9.

265
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:31,320
 So verse 9, "Certainly I will go with you, saith Deborah.

266
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:34,680
 But because of the course or the way that you are taking,

267
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,560
 the honor will not be yours.

268
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:40,480
 For the Lord will deliver Sisera into the hands of a woman."

269
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:43,200
 So Deborah went with Barak to Kadesh.

270
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:46,320
 There, Barak summoned Zebulun and Naphtali,

271
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:49,320
 and 10,000 men went up under his command.

272
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:51,520
 Deborah also went up with him.

273
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:54,480
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

274
00:20:57,120 --> 00:21:23,280
 So there are a few ways for us to understand verse 9 here.

275
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,720
 The most straightforward reading might lead us to think that

276
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:28,640
 because Barak shows some signs of doubt,

277
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:30,400
 God is kind of like changing his mind

278
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:35,160
 to teach Barak a lesson by taking away the honor from him.

279
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:50,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

280
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:51,720
 However, there's actually a better way

281
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:56,240
 to understand this, that this is actually not a punishment

282
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:59,360
 for Barak, rather it is a clarification

283
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:02,040
 of God's initial promise.

284
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:04,920
 God's promise to him still stands,

285
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:08,880
 that victory will still belong to Barak and Israel.

286
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:12,880
 However, Deborah added a crucial detail here in the plot.

287
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:16,240
 Because of the course or because of the way in verse 9

288
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:19,400
 that Barak is taking, the Lord will deliver Sisera

289
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:23,240
 into the hands of a woman, not the military commander

290
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,880
 or his army.

291
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:50,080
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

292
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:52,200
 And despite Barak's incomplete faith,

293
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:55,080
 God chose to show his faithfulness by actually

294
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:58,160
 accommodating to Barak's term, that Deborah will indeed

295
00:22:58,160 --> 00:23:00,440
 go with him into the battle.

296
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:11,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

297
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:13,440
 And then verse 11.

298
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:16,280
 "Now Herber, the Canaanite, had left the other Canaanites,

299
00:23:16,280 --> 00:23:19,880
 the descendants of Hobah, Moses' brother or father-in-law,

300
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:22,240
 and pitched his tent by the great tree

301
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:26,040
 in Zananim near Kadesh."

302
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:37,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

303
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,280
 So this verse right here, verse 11,

304
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:41,800
 we actually find a break in the main storyline.

305
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:44,600
 And we're being introduced to this family

306
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:46,440
 called Herber, the Canaanite.

307
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:48,480
 So even though this verse probably doesn't progress

308
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:51,560
 the plot at this point, but this Canaanite family,

309
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:54,720
 and especially the tent that they live in,

310
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:58,040
 will play an important part later in our story.

311
00:23:58,040 --> 00:23:59,240
 So just keep that in mind.

312
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:16,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

313
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:20,600
 So let's continue with our story in verse 12 to 15.

314
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:23,840
 "When they told Sisera that Barak, son of Abinoam,

315
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:26,280
 had gone up to Mount Tabor, Sisera

316
00:24:26,280 --> 00:24:29,960
 summoned from Harosheth-hagoim to the Kishon River

317
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:33,600
 all his men and his 900 iron chariots.

318
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:36,720
 Then Deborah said to Barak, go.

319
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:40,360
 This is the day the Lord has given Sisera into your hands.

320
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:42,680
 Has not the Lord gone ahead of you?

321
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,880
 And so Barak went down Mount Tabor

322
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:47,200
 with 10,000 men following him.

323
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:50,120
 And at Barak's advance, the Lord routed Sisera

324
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:53,160
 and all his chariots and army by the sword.

325
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:57,080
 And Sisera got down from his chariots and fled on foot."

326
00:24:57,080 --> 00:25:20,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

327
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:36,720
 And so here in verse 14, Deborah once again

328
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:40,920
 reminds Barak of the promised victory from the Lord.

329
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:44,640
 And so not only did she go physically with Barak,

330
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:46,960
 in order to build up his faith, the Lord

331
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:50,520
 also used Deborah to remind and reassure Barak

332
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:53,320
 at opportune times that the Lord had already

333
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:55,880
 given Sisera into his hands.

334
00:25:55,880 --> 00:26:15,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

335
00:26:15,280 --> 00:26:18,520
 And as the Lord promised, we see that he routed the Canaanites

336
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:21,720
 army, and Sisera actually had to abandon his chariots

337
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:23,160
 and flee on foot.

338
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:32,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

339
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:35,840
 And then in verse 16, "Barak pursued the chariots

340
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:38,880
 and his army as far as Harosheth Hagoyim,

341
00:26:38,880 --> 00:26:41,480
 and all Sisera's troops fell by the sword.

342
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,360
 Not a man was left."

343
00:26:43,360 --> 00:26:52,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

344
00:26:52,120 --> 00:26:55,800
 And so if you remember at the beginning of our passage,

345
00:26:55,800 --> 00:27:00,480
 Harosheth Hagoyim is where Sisera and his army was based.

346
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:04,720
 So Sisera's army, they retreated all the way back to their base.

347
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:07,280
 And if you look at the map, Harosheth Hagoyim

348
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:10,280
 is the circle on the left.

349
00:27:10,280 --> 00:27:13,760
 And it is west of Mount Tabor.

350
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:16,920
 And so we know that Barak, in order to pursue them,

351
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:18,360
 he went west.

352
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:20,000
 So keep that in mind again.

353
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:44,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

354
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:50,400
 And verse 17, "Sisera, meanwhile, fled on foot to the tent of Jael,

355
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:53,480
 the wife of Herber the Canaan, because there

356
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:56,040
 was an alliance between Jabin, king of Hazor,

357
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:58,600
 and the family of Herber the Canaan."

358
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:09,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

359
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:13,680
 So this is where the mystery, the information from verse 11

360
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,880
 started to make a little sense.

361
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:19,560
 Here, we're being introduced to another character, Jael,

362
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:23,320
 who is the wife of Herber the Canaan from verse 11.

363
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:36,680
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

364
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:40,680
 And why did Sisera actually flee to the tent of Jael?

365
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:43,760
 We learned that her husband has some sort of political ties

366
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:45,840
 with Jabin, king of Canaan.

367
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:47,920
 And so Sisera, in his mind, he probably

368
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:52,240
 thought that he could get some help from this ally of theirs.

369
00:28:52,240 --> 00:29:06,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

370
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:09,480
 And if you look at the map again, the tent of Jael

371
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:13,240
 is situated in Za'ananim, which is east of Mount Tabor.

372
00:29:13,240 --> 00:29:15,400
 That is the circle on the right.

373
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:25,560
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

374
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:27,760
 Yes, so we know Sisera headed east.

375
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:29,800
 So at this point, we started to get more clarity

376
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:32,640
 on what Deborah means in verse 9.

377
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:35,880
 When she told Barak that because of the course

378
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:38,920
 or because of the way that he is taking--

379
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:41,280
 that is, he is heading west--

380
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:43,680
 the owner would not be his, because Barak

381
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,960
 is literally heading in the wrong direction

382
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,840
 in pursuit of Sisera.

383
00:29:47,840 --> 00:30:05,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

384
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:07,420
 And as for Jael, we don't know much

385
00:30:07,420 --> 00:30:09,920
 about her own political allegiance.

386
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,520
 However, the important thing here

387
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:15,000
 is to know that she is not part of Israel.

388
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:18,080
 And physically, she also lives at least 10 miles away

389
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:19,920
 from the battlefield.

390
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:21,400
 And so this reinforced the narrative

391
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:24,400
 that she is the least likely person, the least likely

392
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:27,180
 character to participate in this battle.

393
00:30:27,180 --> 00:30:28,640
 And yet, her appearance will actually

394
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:31,240
 set the stage for the most unexpected way

395
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:33,200
 the Lord would deliver Israel.

396
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:59,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

397
00:30:59,320 --> 00:31:03,900
 So let's look at verse 18 to 21, "So Jael went out to meet

398
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:07,900
 Sisera and say to him, come, my lord, come right in.

399
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:09,340
 Don't be afraid.

400
00:31:09,340 --> 00:31:13,420
 So he entered her tent, and she covered him with a blanket.

401
00:31:13,420 --> 00:31:14,820
 I am thirsty, he said.

402
00:31:14,820 --> 00:31:16,860
 Please give me some water.

403
00:31:16,860 --> 00:31:19,820
 And so she opened a skin of milk, gave him a drink,

404
00:31:19,820 --> 00:31:21,860
 and covered him up.

405
00:31:21,860 --> 00:31:24,380
 Stand in the doorway of the tent, he told her.

406
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:27,420
 If someone comes by and asks you, is anyone in there,

407
00:31:27,420 --> 00:31:29,200
 say no.

408
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:34,120
 But Jael, Herbert's wife, picked up a tent peg and hammer

409
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:38,860
 and went quietly to him while he lay fast asleep, exhausted.

410
00:31:38,860 --> 00:31:42,500
 She drove the tent peg through his temple into the ground,

411
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:44,260
 and he died."

412
00:31:44,260 --> 00:32:10,580
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

413
00:32:10,580 --> 00:32:25,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

414
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:28,840
 And so now, the promise is fulfilled,

415
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:31,160
 and there is no ambiguity left.

416
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:33,560
 Just as the Lord promised through Deborah,

417
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:37,100
 he delivers Sisera into the hands of a woman.

418
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:40,760
 This woman is not Deborah herself, but it is Jael,

419
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:43,740
 who is the least likely person in this story.

420
00:32:43,740 --> 00:33:01,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

421
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,760
 And then verse 22.

422
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:06,520
 "Just then, Barak came by in pursuit of Sisera,

423
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:08,680
 and Jael went out to meet him.

424
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:10,520
 'Come,' she said, 'I will show you

425
00:33:10,520 --> 00:33:12,560
 the man you are looking for.'

426
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:14,160
 So he went in with her, and there

427
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:18,660
 lay Sisera with the tent peg through his temple, dead."

428
00:33:18,660 --> 00:33:33,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

429
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:36,400
 And so through Jael's invitation into her tent,

430
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:41,960
 Barak himself got to witness how the Lord fulfilled his promise.

431
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:44,200
 And I can imagine that at this moment,

432
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:46,960
 seeing what had happened in front of him,

433
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:49,840
 the commander of the enemy, who had cruelly

434
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:52,360
 oppressed Israel for the past 20 years,

435
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:55,200
 now laying dead on the ground.

436
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:57,680
 Barak probably gained a greater faith and confidence

437
00:33:57,680 --> 00:33:59,720
 in the Lord at this moment.

438
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:22,560
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

439
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:25,160
 And even though Barak shows some signs of spiritual weakness

440
00:34:25,160 --> 00:34:28,240
 and trying to negotiate with God's command,

441
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:30,680
 God, on the other hand, continued to show his patience

442
00:34:30,680 --> 00:34:32,640
 and his faithfulness to Barak.

443
00:34:32,640 --> 00:34:36,360
 And he did so by using both women in the story, Deborah

444
00:34:36,360 --> 00:34:40,560
 as the messenger and Jael as the executor of the promise,

445
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:43,260
 to show Barak that his words never fail

446
00:34:43,260 --> 00:34:45,400
 and he can be fully trusted.

447
00:34:45,400 --> 00:35:12,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

448
00:35:12,120 --> 00:35:13,040
 So let's finish up.

449
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:17,160
 Verse 23, "On that day, God subdued Jabin, king of Canaan,

450
00:35:17,160 --> 00:35:18,800
 before the Israelites.

451
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:21,520
 And the hand of the Israelites pressed harder and harder

452
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:25,160
 against Jabin, king of Canaan, until they destroyed him."

453
00:35:25,160 --> 00:35:35,920
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

454
00:35:35,920 --> 00:35:38,640
 And so here's the main idea that I want us to take away with us

455
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:41,080
 today, that we can lean on the Lord,

456
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:43,720
 even in the midst of adversities or doubts,

457
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:48,360
 because he is trustworthy and his promise never fail.

458
00:35:48,360 --> 00:36:01,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

459
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:04,440
 And this is the invitation that lies before us.

460
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:06,320
 Would you trust him?

461
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:08,440
 Would you hold on to God's promise,

462
00:36:08,440 --> 00:36:11,380
 even when life seems out of control?

463
00:36:11,380 --> 00:36:13,480
 And would you choose the way of Jesus,

464
00:36:13,480 --> 00:36:17,240
 even when it is inconvenient or uncomfortable?

465
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:37,680
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

466
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:40,240
 And so I want to end my sermon by showing the full YouTube

467
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:43,760
 shorts of the mom bringing her daughter to climb.

468
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:46,440
 And as you watch later, I want to draw your attention

469
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:49,120
 to these two very different perspectives,

470
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:53,000
 from the daughter's perspective and the mom's perspective.

471
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,920
 And so from the daughter's perspective,

472
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:57,560
 when she is at the brink of a breakdown,

473
00:36:57,560 --> 00:37:00,580
 her doubts and fears affects her trust in her mom,

474
00:37:00,580 --> 00:37:04,440
 as well as her mom's ability to keep her safe.

475
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:07,560
 But from the mom's perspective, her daughter

476
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:10,040
 is actually never in danger, because she

477
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:12,440
 is right there with her.

478
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:14,880
 And instead of letting the mutual trust of her daughter

479
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:18,400
 to get into her, the mom patiently guides her daughter

480
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:21,680
 step by step and lovingly encourages her

481
00:37:21,680 --> 00:37:23,680
 until she gets to the top.

482
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:51,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

483
00:37:51,960 --> 00:38:04,000
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

484
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:05,160
 So let's watch it together.

485
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:22,040
 Man, nice work, man, oh, great work.

486
00:38:22,040 --> 00:38:31,480
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

487
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:32,480
 Nice, bud.

488
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:38,960
 Great work, buddy.

489
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:46,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

490
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:47,960
 Oh, yeah.

491
00:38:47,960 --> 00:38:54,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

492
00:38:54,960 --> 00:39:01,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

493
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:06,920
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

494
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:10,920
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

495
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:11,920
 To your left, mate.

496
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:12,920
 There you go.

497
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:15,920
 Well done, buddy.

498
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:20,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

499
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:24,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

500
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:28,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

501
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:40,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

502
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:44,400
 So it is the same when it comes to our life.

503
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:47,400
 When we see things from our own limited perspective,

504
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:50,880
 we can easily lose faith when we are confronted

505
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,960
 by our own doubts and fear.

506
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:55,360
 But if we can learn to lean on the Lord

507
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:57,960
 and look at things from His perspective,

508
00:39:57,960 --> 00:39:59,880
 we would know that we can fully trust Him,

509
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:02,320
 because He is always right there with us,

510
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:04,760
 and He is always trustworthy.

511
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:27,920
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

512
00:40:27,920 --> 00:40:30,600
 So, Church, let's continue to grow our faith in Him.

513
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:31,360
 Let's pray.

514
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:35,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

515
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:40,120
 Lord, thank you for being a faithful and trustworthy God.

516
00:40:40,120 --> 00:40:42,480
 We know that your promise never fails,

517
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:46,280
 and we rest in the fact that nothing, nothing can ever

518
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:49,400
 stop you from accomplishing your word.

519
00:40:49,400 --> 00:40:53,200
 So, Lord, increase our faith in you.

520
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:57,640
 Remind us of your goodness and your faithfulness in our life.

521
00:40:57,640 --> 00:40:59,960
 Strengthen us in areas of our life

522
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:03,160
 where our faith is incomplete.

523
00:41:03,160 --> 00:41:06,320
 Heal us of our deepest fear and doubt

524
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:09,840
 so that we can come before you with greater trust.

525
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:30,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

526
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:43,560
 And in Jesus' name, we pray, amen.

527
00:41:43,560 --> 00:41:46,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

528
00:41:46,520 --> 00:41:47,760
 Amen.

529
00:41:47,760 --> 00:41:51,120
 OK, thank you all for joining us this morning.

530
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:52,920
 And as Kelly has mentioned, Pastor Mark

531
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:56,880
 is preaching at Wheaton today, so he won't be with us.

532
00:41:56,880 --> 00:42:00,720
 But I would still encourage you to stay, hang out a little bit,

533
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:02,680
 and connect with one another.

534
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:03,880
 So go in peace.

535
00:42:03,880 --> 00:42:04,440
 You're loved.

536
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:10,340
 you

